# Automerge Setup

> Generated by `/shipwright-adopt` for the **{PROFILE}** stack profile. It lists
> the Required-Check job names that the workflows in *this* repo actually
> produce, so you can wire GitHub branch protection without trial-and-error.
> Safe to edit or delete — re-run adopt to regenerate.

Once this repo is on GitHub with branch protection, you can let
`/shipwright-iterate` PRs merge themselves when every Required Check is green,
instead of clicking merge by hand. This is GitHub-native auto-merge — no bot,
no polling loop.

## 1. Required Checks in this repo

Branch protection matches on the **GitHub check name** (the rendered job name),
**not** the workflow file name. These are the checks the scaffolded workflows
produce:

{REQUIRED_CHECKS_TABLE}

> **The dormant trap.** Shipwright ships `ci.yml` / `security.yml` / `codeql.yml`
> *dormant* (only `workflow_dispatch:` active) so they don't fire before you've
> reviewed Phase-B activation. A dormant workflow's check **never reports**, so
> requiring it in branch protection would block *every* PR forever. Activate the
> `pull_request:` trigger (uncomment it in the workflow file) **before** you add
> that workflow's job name as a Required Check.

## 2. Activate the workflows you want to require

For each dormant workflow above, edit the file under `.github/workflows/` and
uncomment its `pull_request:` trigger block. Commit, open a throwaway PR, and
confirm the check appears and goes green. (`security.yml` activation also has
`docs/security-ci-setup.md` if your repo has it.)

`claude-review.yml` already fires on PRs; it is **advisory** (it posts a review
comment and never fails the check) and needs an `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` repo secret
to produce output. Requiring it just guarantees the review ran.

## 3. Configure branch protection (GitHub UI)

**Settings → Branches → Add branch ruleset** (or *Branch protection rules*) for
`main`:

- ☑ **Require a pull request before merging** — Required approvals: **0**
  (Shipwright's local Step-8 review + the checks below are the gate; a solo
  maintainer has no second approver).
- ☑ **Require status checks to pass before merging** → add each Required-Check
  name from the table above **that you activated** in step 2. Type the name
  exactly (copy from a real PR's checks list to avoid typos).
- ☑ **Require branches to be up to date before merging**.
- ☑ **Do not allow bypassing the above settings** (optional; include
  administrators if you want the rule to apply to your own pushes too).

> Do **not** enable *Require signed commits* / `required_signatures`:
> `/shipwright-iterate` PRs are committed headless without a signing key, so
> requiring signatures would leave every iterate PR permanently `BLOCKED` and
> silently kill automerge. The squash commit GitHub creates on `main` is
> verified on its own.

## 4. Enable auto-merge

**Settings → General → Pull Requests → ☑ Allow auto-merge.**

## 5. Arm auto-merge on a PR

```bash
gh pr merge --auto --squash --delete-branch <pr-number>
```

GitHub merges the PR automatically once all Required Checks are green. If a
check goes red, the PR sits "auto-merge armed, waiting" — fix it and push; the
merge fires on the next green run. `/shipwright-iterate`'s finalization can arm
this for you on `iterate/*` branches.

## Notes

- **CodeQL is GitHub's paid SAST on private repos** (free on public). The
  scaffolded `security.yml` (Semgrep + Trivy + Gitleaks + Shipwright's
  prompt-injection scan) is the **free** default and scans *more*; CodeQL is the
  GitHub-Advanced-Security alternative. You don't need both — pick the path that
  fits your plan, and only require the checks for the path you run. See
  `docs/security-ci-setup.md` (Path A vs Path B) if present.
- **Anti-ratchet bloat-check is NOT scaffolded.** Shipwright's monorepo runs a
  `bloat-check.yml` (`Anti-ratchet + allowlist diff`) Required Check, but it
  depends on the framework's own anti-ratchet runner which isn't vendored into
  adopted repos. If you want that discipline, it's a manual opt-in for now (a
  follow-up will package it). It is not required for automerge.
